001.comments: Visit cnrs.ubc.ca for full course descriptions. Cross-listed with LATN 502C. It is recommended that students have taken LATN 350 and/or LATN 351 prior to registering for this course.Visit https://cnrs.ubc.ca/fall2020courses/ for information on course delivery.

description: Studies in narrative verse, comedy, satire, elegiac and lyric poetry. May be repeated for up to 12 credits. It is recommended that the corequisite course be completed prior to LATN 402.
